273
00:21:10,736 --> 00:21:11,937
- [Jeff] Railroad tracks.

274
00:21:11,937 --> 00:21:14,139
- That's exactly what it is, captain.

275
00:21:15,874 --> 00:21:17,709
- There's a huge French plantation

276
00:21:17,709 --> 00:21:20,045
on the other side of the border.

277
00:21:20,045 --> 00:21:21,947
They're running a small gauge railway,

278
00:21:21,947 --> 00:21:24,249
supposedly to haul out the rubber.

279
00:21:24,249 --> 00:21:26,685
- I've repeatedly asked for an airstrike

280
00:21:26,685 --> 00:21:31,590
to disable that line, but MACV always denies me.

281
00:21:31,590 --> 00:21:32,424
- Why?

282
00:21:33,659 --> 00:21:34,726
- It's in Cambodia.

283
00:21:42,301 --> 00:21:45,837
- All right, Ropes, I think I gotcha this time.

284
00:21:45,837 --> 00:21:48,273
Lucky sevens over kings, buddy.

285
00:21:48,273 --> 00:21:50,342
(laughing)

286
00:21:50,342 --> 00:21:53,045
Well, I guess I'll just start counting this money,

287
00:21:53,045 --> 00:21:54,780
go on over to the PX and buy myself some--

288
00:21:54,780 --> 00:21:56,882
- Wait a minute, wait a minute.

289
00:21:56,882 --> 00:21:58,517
Come back anytime, sweetheart.

290
00:22:00,018 --> 00:22:01,520
There you go, captain, read 'em and weep.

291
00:22:01,520 --> 00:22:03,722
- No, no no no no no.

292
00:22:03,722 --> 00:22:05,390
You shit-canned me again.

293
00:22:05,390 --> 00:22:07,492
- No way, captain, no way.

294
00:22:07,492 --> 00:22:09,928
Marty open all night long.

295
00:22:09,928 --> 00:22:11,630
- Attention.

296
00:22:11,630 --> 00:22:13,365
- At ease, gentlemen.

297
00:22:15,634 --> 00:22:17,703
That your money, marine?

298
00:22:17,703 --> 00:22:18,537
- Yes, sir.

299
00:22:19,504 --> 00:22:21,006
- Better get it off the table.

300
00:22:24,042 --> 00:22:28,547
Well I got bad news, men, Firebase Maryland is gone.

301
00:22:30,148 --> 00:22:32,384
I know a lot of you had buddies up there.

302
00:22:33,518 --> 00:22:35,320
The trouble is the numb nuts at the desks

303
00:22:35,320 --> 00:22:37,823
make us fight with our mittens on.

304
00:22:37,823 --> 00:22:41,193
You think Ho Chi Minh does that to his troops?

305
00:22:43,762 --> 00:22:45,464
Anybody recognize this territory?

306
00:22:46,665 --> 00:22:47,799
- That's Cambodia, sir.

307
00:22:48,700 --> 00:22:50,102
- That's right.

308
00:22:50,102 --> 00:22:51,770
I've been interrogating prisoners.

309
00:22:53,238 --> 00:22:56,374
It seems they've got a supply line just across the border

310
00:22:56,374 --> 00:22:59,845
they're using as a springboard every time they hit us.

311
00:22:59,845 --> 00:23:02,347
- All our problems can be traced right back to that.

312
00:23:03,715 --> 00:23:05,217
- You never would have lost Lennox

313
00:23:05,217 --> 00:23:07,753
if we'd been allowed to make a preemptive strike.

314
00:23:07,753 --> 00:23:09,654
- Well why don't we hit them mothers then?

315
00:23:09,654 --> 00:23:11,757
- Yeah, where does it say we always gotta play clean?

316
00:23:11,757 --> 00:23:13,125
Come on, captain.

317
00:23:13,125 --> 00:23:14,493
- Come on, let's go for it.

318
00:23:17,362 --> 00:23:20,832
- Sir, if you wanna take out the NVA commander

319
00:23:20,832 --> 00:23:23,468
who's running the show in our sector,

320
00:23:23,468 --> 00:23:26,238
I can give you a highly motivated top notch LRRP team.

321
00:23:28,006 --> 00:23:30,575
- Any of you speak the local lingo?

322
00:23:30,575 --> 00:23:32,010
- No, sir. - Not me.

323
00:23:32,010 --> 00:23:34,513
- Sir, how about Sergeant Park?

324
00:23:36,782 --> 00:23:38,316
- Good idea.

325
00:23:38,316 --> 00:23:41,019
- All you gotta do is give the go ahead, sir.

326
00:23:41,019 --> 00:23:42,387
Let's get it done.

327
00:23:42,387 --> 00:23:43,588
- We'll never get the nod if we go

328
00:23:43,588 --> 00:23:44,890
for an official clearance.

329
00:23:46,725 --> 00:23:50,829
- Captain, you know I can't order you to do this,

330
00:23:50,829 --> 00:23:52,631
this is strictly off the shelf.

331
00:23:54,132 --> 00:23:55,634
You men are the best I've got.

332
00:23:57,202 --> 00:24:00,872
- Anybody wants out, speak up now.

333
00:24:00,872 --> 00:24:02,474
- Payback time.

334
00:24:02,474 --> 00:24:05,243
Payback time is payback time.

335
00:24:05,243 --> 00:24:08,914
- Captain Holland, your job is to seek out those tracks

336
00:24:08,914 --> 00:24:09,781
and destroy them.

337
